Extract the most MS2 intense scan

extract_MS2.Rd

This function takes raw MS2 signal and looks for the most intense scan and proceed to extracts the MS2 spectra. Additionally, it plots the MS2 TIC chromatogram and color in red the most intense scan.

Usage

extract_MS2(spec, verbose = TRUE, out_list = FALSE)

Arguments

spec

a data frame with the MS2 spectra

verbose

a boolean indicating if the MS2 TIC chromatogram is displayed

out_list

a boolean expressing if the output is a list containing the MS2 spectra plus the TIC chromatogram (verbose = TRUE), or only the data frame with the MS2 spectra (verbose = FALSE).

Examples

# Importing the Spectrum of Procyanidin A2 in negative ionzation mode
# and 20 eV as the collision energy
ProcA2_file <- system.file("extdata",
                       "ProcyanidinA2_neg_20eV.mzXML",
                        package = "MS2extract")

# Region of interest table (rt in seconds)
ProcA2_data <- data.frame(Formula = "C30H24O12",Ionization_mode = "Negative",
                     min_rt = 163, max_rt = 180)
# Importing MS2 data
ProcA2_raw <- import_mzxml(ProcA2_file, ProcA2_data)
#> Reading MS2 data from ProcyanidinA2_neg_20eV.mzXML
#> Processing...

# Extracting most intense scan ----
# Returning plot + MS2 spectra
extract_MS2(ProcA2_raw)
